caller_intent: Brian wants to obtain the cheapest liability coverage for his 2004 Lexus RX 330 and needs proof of insurance sent via text or email.
resolution_steps: Agent Gary confirms Brian's request for liability coverage and notes it's the cheapest option.
Asks for car details (model: 2004 Lexus RX 330) after initial confusion about the make.
Acknowledges missing VIN but states he'll follow up with another agent who previously spoke to Brian.
Offers to send proof of insurance via text or email, confirming Brian's email address (Simmons_Services@Outlook.com).
Agrees to prioritize text message delivery, with email as a backup.
knowledge_required: Customer communication protocols (text/email delivery of documents)
systems_referenced: Internal communication tools (text/email for proof of insurance delivery)
summary: Gary from Alliance Insurance Services helps Brian set up liability insurance for his 2004 Lexus RX 330. Despite missing a VIN, Gary commits to follow up with another agent and arranges proof of insurance delivery via text or email. Brian confirms his email address and agrees to the plan.
